<!-- ──────────────── 04 DEEPTECH FOCUS ──────────────── -->
<section class="sec sec--ink" id="deeptech">
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="sec__head">
      <div class="sec__num">04 · DeepTech focus</div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="sec__title">Five pillars. <em>Three days.</em> One programme.</h2>
        <p class="sec__lead">
          DeepTech as a thematic arc, reweighted each year. Each edition leans differently across the five pillars. The 2027 programme places focus on agents, blockchain infrastructure and applied AI.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="pillars">
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar__code">P / 01</div>
        <h3 class="pillar__name">AI</h3>
        <p class="pillar__desc">Application in operations, regulated markets and business models. Where prototypes become production.</p>
        <div class="pillar__rule">Operations · Markets · Models</div>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar__code">P / 02</div>
        <h3 class="pillar__name">Agents</h3>
        <p class="pillar__desc">Autonomous systems in enterprise use. What works, what breaks, what governance looks like.</p>
        <div class="pillar__rule">Enterprise · Governance</div>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar__code">P / 03</div>
        <h3 class="pillar__name">Quantum</h3>
        <p class="pillar__desc">From research lab to productive application. The honest state of post-classical computing.</p>
        <div class="pillar__rule">Research · Application</div>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar__code">P / 04</div>
        <h3 class="pillar__name">Cyber Security</h3>
        <p class="pillar__desc">Resilience in an agentic world. New attack surfaces, new defences, new responsibilities.</p>
        <div class="pillar__rule">Resilience · Defence</div>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar__code">P / 05</div>
        <h3 class="pillar__name">Blockchain</h3>
        <p class="pillar__desc">Infrastructure, identity, tokenization, custody and new market architectures. Technology, not trading.</p>
        <div class="pillar__rule">Infrastructure · Identity</div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="note-block">
      <strong>A note on Blockchain.</strong> &nbsp;On the Industry Days, Blockchain stands for technology and infrastructure, not for crypto trading. Crypto topics appear where they have technological or business substance. This distinction is deliberate. It is what sets the Industry Days apart from a pure crypto event.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
